<DOC><DOCNO> AP891218-0166 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-18-89 1907EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-WeatherpageWeather     12-18 0336</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Weatherpage Weather,0347</SECOND><HEAD>Snow Falls Across Northern Tier Of States, More Record Lows</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Snow fell Monday from Washington state to Maine and winter-likeweather threatened the Southeast, and more low temperature recordswere set across the Midwest.   Balmy Miami beckoned with a record high of 87 degrees.   Elsewhere, record lows were 1 below zero at Binghamton, N.Y.; 5below at Cleveland; 3 below at Cincinnati; 7 below at Columbus,Ohio; 3 below at Detroit; 5 below at Fort Wayne, Ind.; 1 below atLexington, Ky.; 3 below at Mansfield, Ohio; 4 below at Parkersburg,W.Va.; 7 below at Pittsburgh; and 8 below at Youngstown, Ohio.Elsewhere Redding, Calif., hit a record low of 24.   At midday, light snow fell from eastern Washington intonorthwestern Montana and over parts of Idaho, Colorado, SouthDakota, Nebraska, Kansas, Missouri, Iowa, Michigan, upstate NewYork, Vermont and Maine.   In the Southeast, bitter cold and slippery roads closed hundredsof schools. Ice was believed to blame for an accident outsideAtlanta in which one man was killed.   A winter storm warning was posted through the night and intoTuesday over the mountains, foothills and piedmont of SouthCarolina.   Snow and winter weather advisories were in effect into Tuesdayfor parts of Kentucky, Ohio, North Caroline, and Georgia.   New snow accumulations at Colorado ski resorts included 16inches at Vail, 10 inches at Steamboat, 9{ inches at Breckenridge,and 8 inches at Loveland and Mary Jane, the National WeatherService reported.   Steamboat Springs has received 99 inches of snow in nine days, aspokeswoman said.   Rain was scattered over central Texas and the upper Texas GulfCoast, southern Louisiana, southern Mississippi, the FloridaPanhandle, northeastern Florida, eastern Georgia and southern SouthCarolina.   Freezing rain extended from central Arkansas across centralLouisiana.   Temperatures around the nation at 3 p.m. EST ranged from 13degrees below zero at Havre, Mont., to 87 at Miami. Mondaymorning's low for the Lower 48 states was 31 below zero at Warroad,Minn.</TEXT></DOC>